# Whitelist .gitignore.
#
# Claude Code continuously writes runtime state into this directory, so the
# default is to ignore everything at the root and opt in explicitly. A new
# state dir appearing in `git status --ignored` after a CC update is the safety
# net working, not a problem: tracking it requires a deliberate decision.

# Ignore everything at the top level by default...
/*

# ...except these tracked items:
!.gitignore
!.gitattributes
!README.md
!CLAUDE.md
!CLAUDE_webchat.md
!NEW-MACHINE-SETUP.md
!VKBASALT-SETUP.md
!settings.json
!statusline.sh
!commands
!scripts
!skills
!briefs

# Defense-in-depth: never track these even if the pattern logic above ever slips.
.credentials.json
history.jsonl
SECRET-SAUCE.md
HARDWARE-NOTES.md
CLAUDE_webchat.expanded.md
